of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred ferch Gruffudd was born about 1145, in Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Richard d' Aldford. She died in 1230, at the age of 86."},"et":{"about 1145–1230":"umbes 1145–1230","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1195–1235":"1195–1235","1145–1230":"1145–1230","1213":"1213","1235":"1235","1145":"1145","1230":"1230","about 1145":"umbes 1145","1195":"1195",",Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Runcorn, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Runcorn, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1145–1230":"noin 1145–1230","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1195–1235":"1195–1235","1145–1230":"1145–1230","1213":"1213","1235":"1235","1145":"1145","1230":"1230","about 1145":"noin 1145","1195":"1195",",Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Runcorn, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Runcorn, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1145–1230":"environ 1145–1230","1145–1213":"1145–1213","1195–1235":"1195–1235","1145–1230":"1145–1230","1213":"1213","1235":"1235","1145":"1145","1230":"1230","about 1145":"environ 1145","1195":"1195",",Wa